, weak regression coverage, or mismatches between synapse ingestion, anchor mapping, coupling assembly, and the documentation that later simulator milestones will rely on.\\nagent_tickets/milestone_7_synapse_coupling_tickets.md:154:- The verification pass checks contract compatibility across the synapse registry, anchor mapping artifacts, coupling bundles, inspection tooling, manifest discovery, and fallback behavior for mixed morphology classes.\\nagent_tickets/milestone_7_synapse_coupling_tickets.md:161:- `python3 scripts/run_agent_tickets.py --tickets-file agent_tickets/milestone_7_synapse_coupling_tickets.md --ticket-id FW-M7-006 --dry-run`\\nagent_tickets/milestone_7_synapse_coupling_tickets.md:165:This ticket should run after the earlier Milestone 7 tickets are complete. The main deliverable is confidence: one place where a reviewer can see that the synapse-to-coupling milestone is integrated, documented, and ready for downstream simulator work.\\ndocs/milestones.md:33:- **Grant** owns the wave model, discretization choices, coupling assumptions, stability reasoning, and validation logic  \\ndocs/milestones.md:38:  - synapse coupling API  \\ndocs/milestones.md:65:- define operators and coupling  \\ndocs/milestones.md:93:| 7 | Map synapses and define inter-neuron coupling | Shared leaning math-physics (45/55) | Shared lead | Patch-level coupling model |\\ndocs/milestones.md:386:- flagging missing metadata needed for later coupling/model design\\ndocs/milestones.md:527:## Milestone 7 — Map synapses and define inter-neuron coupling\\ndocs/milestones.md:540:- whether coupling is:  \\ndocs/milestones.md:552:- serializing coupling maps  \\ndocs/milestones.md:553:- coupling inspection tools\\ndocs/milestones.md:557:- defining coupling kernels  \\ndocs/milestones.md:560:- determining whether coupling is instantaneous, filtered, nonlinear, etc.\\ndocs/milestones.md:566:- coupling rules are configurable and versioned\\ndocs/milestones.md:791:- routing between coupling modes\\ndocs/milestones.md:969:- coupling mode  \\ndocs/milestones.md:978:- no lateral coupling  \\ndocs/milestones.md:1129:### Phase 3 — Circuit coupling and inputs\\ndocs/milestones.md:1140:- coupling kernels  \\ndocs/milestones.md:1287:- keeping the operators and coupling scientifically honest  \\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T222203Z/FW-M7-001_Freeze_a_versioned_synapse_asset_contract_and_inter-neuron_coupling_design_note/stdout.jsonl:51:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_25\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '527,580p' docs/milestones.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"## Milestone 7 — Map synapses and define inter-neuron coupling\\n\\n**Workload split:** Shared, leaning math/physics  \\n**Suggested lead:** Shared\\n\\n### Goal\\n\\nTurn connectome edges into transfers between neuron surface states.\\n\\n### Need to define\\n\\n- where synaptic input lands on the receiving surface  \\n- where output is read on the presynaptic neuron  \\n- whether coupling is:  \\n  - point-to-point  \\n  - patch-to-patch  \\n  - distributed patch cloud  \\n- how synaptic sign and delay are handled  \\n- how multiple synapses aggregate\\n\\n### Jack owns\\n\\n- synapse table processing  \\n- locating nearest patches / skeleton nodes  \\n- building fast lookup structures  \\n- serializing coupling maps  \\n- coupling inspection tools\\n\\n### Grant owns\\n\\n- defining coupling kernels  \\n- choosing delay models  \\n- deciding how synaptic transfer modifies the surface state  \\n- determining whether coupling is instantaneous, filtered, nonlinear, etc.\\n\\n### Done when\\n\\n- any edge can be inspected and visualized  \\n- the simulator knows where and how input transfers between neurons  \\n- coupling rules are configurable and versioned\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Milestone 8 — Build the visual input stack\\n\\nThis milestone is intentionally split because different parts belong to different people.\\n\\n### Milestone 8A — Canonical stimulus library\\n\\n**Workload split:** Programming-heavy  \\n**Suggested lead:** Jack\\n\\nBuild generators for:\\n\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T222203Z/FW-M7-001_Freeze_a_versioned_synapse_asset_contract_and_inter-neuron_coupling_design_note/stdout.jsonl:54:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_27\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"Plan:\\n1. Add a library-owned Milestone 7 coupling contract module with deterministic path builders, manifest metadata builders/parsers, and discovery helpers.\\n2. Thread the new contract into the processed manifest writer so every record and manifest header exposes the version, design note, synapse registry pointer, anchor-map paths, and coupling bundle discovery without altering existing geometry/operator fields.\\n3. Add the decisive Milestone 7 design note and update `docs/pipeline_notes.md` to document the new contract alongside the existing bundle contracts.\\n4. Extend regression coverage with default-manifest assertions plus a focused deterministic serialization/discovery test for fixture coupling metadata.\\n5. Run the focused test and `make test`, then fix anything surfaced.\"}}\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T222203Z/FW-M7-001_Freeze_a_versioned_synapse_asset_contract_and_inter-neuron_coupling_design_note/stdout.jsonl:74:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_43\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,120p' src/flywire_wave/geometry_contract.py\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"from __future__ import annotations\\n\\nimport copy\\nimport json\\nimport math\\nfrom collections.abc import Mapping\\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\nfrom .coupling_contract import (\\n    COUPLING_BUNDLE_CONTRACT_VERSION,\\n    build_coupling_bundle_metadata,\\n    build_coupling_contract_manifest_metadata,\\n    parse_coupling_bundle_me