{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_85","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba docs/pipeline_notes.md | sed -n '20,130p'\"","aggregated_output":"    20\t\n    21\tMilestone 4 subset generation writes one artifact bundle per named preset under\n    22\t`data/interim/subsets/<preset>/`:\n    23\t\n    24\t- `root_ids.txt`: simulator-facing root-id list\n    25\t- `selected_neurons.csv`: filtered registry rows for the preset\n    26\t- `subset_stats.json`: graph counts, role counts, and boundary summaries\n    27\t- `subset_manifest.json`: resolved selection rules plus the selected neuron roster\n    28\t- `preview.md`: lightweight Markdown/Mermaid preview for quick inspection\n    29\t\n    30\tThe active preset also refreshes the path named by `config.paths.selected_root_ids`\n    31\tso downstream pipeline steps can switch subsets without code changes. When\n    32\t`config.paths.synapse_source_csv` is configured, the same active-preset write\n    33\talso refreshes `config.paths.processed_coupling_dir/synapse_registry.csv` so\n    34\tthe canonical local synapse table stays aligned with the active selected roots.\n    35\t\n    36\t### Geometry handoff contract\n    37\t\n    38\tMilestone 5 uses the versioned geometry bundle contract\n    39\t`geometry_bundle.v1`. One canonical library path builder owns the\n    40\tfilenames below, and both `scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py` plus\n    41\t`scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py` use it directly.\n    42\t\n    43\tPer neuron, the bundle layout is:\n    44\t\n    45\t- `config.paths.meshes_raw_dir/<root_id>.ply`: raw mesh\n    46\t- `config.paths.skeletons_raw_dir/<root_id>.swc`: raw skeleton\n    47\t- `config.paths.processed_mesh_dir/<root_id>.ply`: simplified mesh\n    48\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_graph.npz`: surface graph\n    49\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_fine_operator.npz`: fine surface operator\n    50\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_patch_graph.npz`: patch graph\n    51\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_coarse_operator.npz`: Galerkin coarse patch operator\n    52\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_descriptors.json`: derived descriptor sidecar\n    53\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_qa.json`: QA sidecar\n    54\t\n    55\tThe processed graph archives intentionally separate fine and coarse data:\n    56\t\n    57\t- the surface graph stores the simplified mesh vertices/faces, sparse surface adjacency/Laplacian arrays, and `surface_to_patch` so every surface vertex has an explicit coarse patch assignment\n    58\t- the fine operator archive stores cotangent stiffness and mass-normalized operator matrices plus explicit supporting geometry including edge lengths/weights, lumped mass, normals, tangent frames, boundary masks, anisotropy coefficients (`anisotropy_vertex_tensor_diagonal`, `anisotropy_edge_direction_uv`, `anisotropy_edge_multiplier`, `effective_cotangent_weights`), and capped edge-geodesic neighborhoods\n    59\t- the patch graph stores sparse coarse adjacency/Laplacian arrays plus `patch_sizes`, `patch_centroids`, `patch_seed_vertices`, and CSR-style `member_vertex_indices` / `member_vertex_indptr` arrays for reconstructing patch membership deterministically\n    60\t- the coarse operator archive stores patch mass / area, Galerkin-projected stiffness, the mass-normalized coarse operator, and the quality metrics used to compare coarse and fine application\n    61\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_transfer_operators.npz` stores explicit fine/coarse transfer structure, physical-field restriction / prolongation matrices, normalized-state transfer operators, and transfer-quality metrics\n    62\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_operator_metadata.json` records the realized discretization family, fallback mode, versioned `operator_assembly` config, boundary mode, anisotropy model, geodesic-neighborhood settings, transfer availability, coarse assembly rule, and coarse-versus-fine quality metrics for downstream discovery\n    63\t\n    64\t`config.paths.manifest_json` records the bundle contract version, dataset,\n    65\tmaterialization version, an explicit meshing-config snapshot including\n    66\t`meshing.operator_assembly`, and per-root asset\n    67\tstatuses/paths. Raw fetch runs also record `raw_asset_provenance` per\n    68\troot ID so cache hits, refetches, skips, validation failures, and\n    69\toptional skeleton fetch errors can be audited without reading console\n    70\tlogs. Processed bundle records also expose `artifact_sources` so each\n    71\tsimplified mesh, surface graph, patch graph, and sidecar points back to\n    72\tthe raw mesh and skeleton inputs it was built against.\n    73\t\n    74\tDescriptor and QA rationale:\n    75\t\n    76\t- `docs/geometry_descriptor_qa.md` documents the default `meshing.qa_thresholds`\n    77\t  profile, what each descriptor bucket is meant to capture, and which failed\n    78\t  checks should block downstream use by default.\n    79\t\n    80\tCompatibility shim:\n    81\t\n    82\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_meta.json` is still written as\n    83\t  a legacy metadata pointer so older consumers can keep reading the prior\n    84\t  sidecar name during migration.\n    85\t- `docs/operator_bundle_design.md` is the authoritative Milestone 6 operator\n    86\t  decision note; later tickets should cite it instead of re-litigating the\n    87\t  default discretization family.\n    88\t\n    89\t### Synapse and coupling handoff contract\n    90\t\n    91\tMilestone 7 now reserves one explicit synapse/coupling discovery surface under\n    92\tthe versioned contract `coupling_bundle.v1`.\n    93\t\n    94\tThe canonical layout is:\n    95\t\n    96\t- `config.paths.processed_coupling_dir/synapse_registry.csv`: local,\n    97\t  simulator-facing synapse registry owned by the library contract\n    98\t- `config.paths.processed_coupling_dir/roots/<root_id>_incoming_anchor_map.npz`:\n    99\t  postsynaptic landing-anchor lookup for one root\n   100\t- `config.paths.processed_coupling_dir/roots/<root_id>_outgoing_anchor_map.npz`:\n   101\t  presynaptic readout-anchor lookup for one root\n   102\t- `config.paths.processed_coupling_dir/roots/<root_id>_coupling_index.json`:\n   103\t  root-local coupling discovery index that can enumerate realized edge bundles\n   104\t- `config.paths.processed_coupling_dir/edges/<pre_root_id>__to__<post_root_id>_coupling.npz`:\n   105\t  canonical edge-level coupling bundle path\n   106\t\n   107\tRegistry-layer materialization notes:\n   108\t\n   109\t- `config.paths.synapse_source_csv` is the explicit per-synapse local snapshot\n   110\t  input when available\n   111\t- the registry loader normalizes source aliases into one canonical synapse\n   112\t  schema and requires `pre_root_id`, `post_root_id`, plus at least one complete\n   113\t  localization field set (`x/y/z`, `pre_x/pre_y/pre_z`, or\n   114\t  `post_x/post_y/post_z`)\n   115\t- `config.paths.processed_coupling_dir/synapse_registry_provenance.json` is the\n   116\t  audit sidecar for the current canonical local synapse registry\n   117\t- subset extraction keeps only rows where both endpoints are in the requested\n   118\t  root set so grouping the synapse registry by `(pre_root_id, post_root_id,\n   119\t  neuropil, nt_type)` reproduces the same-scope edge-level `syn_count`\n   120\t\n   121\t`config.paths.manifest_json` now also records:\n   122\t\n   123\t- `_coupling_contract_version` and `_coupling_contract` at the manifest header\n   124\t- a per-root `coupling_bundle` block that points to the local synapse registry,\n   125\t  root-local anchor maps, the root-local coupling index, and any explicit\n   126\t  edge-bundle references already built for that root\n   127\t- the design-note path and design-note version each bundle conforms to\n   128\t\n   129\tThe default Milestone 7 semantics are intentionally fixed early:\n   130\t\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
